\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. N. candida }C. Presl in J. & C. Presl,{\i  Del. Prag.} 224 (1822) ({\i N. fennica} Mela, {\i Castalia candida} (C. Presl) Schinz & Thell.). Like {\b 1} but usually slightly smaller in all its parts; flowers 6-11 cm in diameter; receptacle weakly 4-angled; filament of innermost stamens lanceolate, wider than the anther; stigma concave, with 6-14 rays; seeds 3·5 mm. 2n = 112, c. 160.{\i  N., N.E. & N.C. Europe, extending locally to E. France, S.W. Romania and S.E. Russia.} Au Be Cz Fe Ga Ge †He Ho No Po Rm Rs(N, B, C, W, E) Su.
\par 

