\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. N. lutea }(L.) Sm. in Sibth. & Sm., Fl. Graec. Prodr. 1: 361 (1809) (Nymphaea lutea L., Nymphosanthus luteus (L.) Fernald). Floating leaves 12-40 × 9-30 cm, ovate, with a deep, acute basal sinus; submerged leaves thin, cordate, with wider sinus. Flowers borne above the water, 4-6 cm in diameter, smelling of alcohol. Sepals 2-3 cm, obovate, persistent, 3 times as long as the broadly spathulate petals. Disc of stigma entire; rays 15-20, not quite reaching its margin. Seeds 5 mm. 2n = 34. Almost throughout Europe. All except Az Bl Co Cr Fa Is Rs(K) Sb; extinct in Si.
